    retrofit:evidence "CORRECTED MECHANISM, conclusion still holds, re-verified 2026-07-21: original evidence text ('write_receipt independent of ggen-constitution-pack') is now factually stale -- merged commit 8c9edb3e4 (PR #316) added a real ccn:Law/ccn:mechanized SPARQL query to sync.rs::write_receipt, emitting one AdmissionItem per constitutional law found. But the code deliberately hardcodes AdmissionDecision::Admitted on BOTH branches (mechanized true or false), with an explicit comment: 'it must not flip the derived Andon level (that would overclaim a live verification that doesn't exist)'. praxis-core::law::DefaultLaw::admit remains fully independent of ggen-constitution-pack (zero references), confirmed unchanged. Net: facts are consulted and mirrored into the receipt's obligation list (a real, if inert, improvement over pure disconnection), but by design still never change the pass/fail decision or Andon level -- the SPOF's substantive claim holds, Accepted standing correct given this is an honestly-disclosed, deliberate non-enforcement choice (the same discipline as the ccn:mechanized=false laws), not a hidden defect." .

